Ilm-aclides, is, m., a native of Syracuse, who, after the expulsion of the younger Dionysius from Sicily, raised a faction against Dion, in whose hands the sovereign power was lodged. He was put to death by Dion's command—a circumstance which contributed in no small degree to alienate from Dion the affections of the Syra- cusans.
